radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal atelectasis at the lung bases. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. Appendix is dilated up to 1.1 cm, with wall thickening, mucosal hyper enhancement and surrounding fat stranding, consistent with acute appendicitis. Small gastric diverticulum. Normal findings in liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, gastrointestinal tract, urinary bladder, and reproductive organs. No lymphadenopathy or significant vascular abnormalities.
